data.title: anchored micronemal antigen is essential for parasite transmission through the mosquito host
data.meta_description: Plasmodium parasites, the eukaryotic pathogens that cause malaria, feature three distinct invasive forms tailored to the host environment they must navigate and invade for life cycle progression. One conserved feature of these invasive forms is the micronemes, apically oriented secretory organelles …
